4. Finding the Largest Number in an Array

Algorithm:

1. Start.


2. Input array arr and size n.


3. Initialize largest = arr[0].


4. For each element in arr:

If the element > largest, update largest.



5. Output largest.


6. End.



Pseudocode:

Start
Input n
Input array arr of size n
largest ← arr[0]
For i ← 1 to n-1 do
    If arr[i] > largest then
        largest ← arr[i]
    End If
End For
Output largest
End
